(825, '最響カミズモード！', 'null', NULL, 'Dai Mugen once held an unmatched passion for playing the drums. However, after being defeated by rival drummer Rin Tanba in a competition, he is left questioning where his heart lies and quits as a result.<br>\n<br>\nOne day, Dai has a fateful encounter with a strange creature named Goutetsu, a self-proclaimed \"god.\" Spotting the boy\'s hidden potential, Goutetsu quickly appoints Dai as his \"oyakata\"—a coach who can guide Goutetsu in the world of \"kamizumo,\" the battles between gods through sumo wrestling. Within kamizumo matches, the gods are powered through the drumbeats struck by their oyakata, which forces Dai to pick up the mallets once more.<br>\n<br>\nAs the duo slowly racks up victories, Dai confronts his self-doubts and reignites his passion in the new endeavor to stand on kamizumo\'s topmost stage.<br>\n<br>\n(Source: MAL Rewrite)<br>\n<br>\n<i>Note: Each episode originally streamed split into two parts and later as a full version.</i>', 0, 1, '', 'japan', 'FALL', 2020, '{\"day\":28,\"month\":9,\"year\":2020}', 'FINISHED', 2, 1, 13, 52, 122632, '2021-11-30 11:17:57', 'https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx122632-nwu9D6gnbThG.jpg', '2021-12-07 02:52:32', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/lbunPmtDPJo'),
(826, 'The Gymnastics Samurai', '体操ザムライ', NULL, 'Joutarou Aragaki, former member of the national team, had given his whole life for gymnastics and was fighting against his age and physical strength. However, one day he is told by his coach to start thinking of his next career. Joutarou struggles, but his daughter, Rei, is always there by his side. But with one fateful encounter, the Aragakis’ lives change drastically.\n<br><br>\n(Source: Funimation)\n', 0, 1, 'Taiso Samurai', 'japan', 'FALL', 2020, '{\"day\":11,\"month\":10,\"year\":2020}', 'FINISHED', 213, 1, 23, 11, 122807, '2021-11-30 11:17:57', 'https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/122807-WuQXmiTg70lh.jpg', '2021-12-07 02:52:32', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/lbunPmtDPJo'),
